Tonight, John Mead's True Believers, a large band with two guitarist, bass guitar, drums, baritone, tenor and alto sax, and trumpet, celebrates the approach of Mardi Gras with music of Little Feat and more!  Buy tickets with cash at the door two hours before sold-out shows, or buy in advance online.  See Martyr's website for schedules and more.  Laissez bon temps roulez!

What is not to like at Martyrs'?! This venue is a Chicago staple that has been showcasing music seven nights a week for the last twenty years. These guys know how to do it right. From the carefully placed gig posters that line the front windows to the amazing sounds that come from the speakers, this place is where its at for live music. I have never seen a bad show here. The staff is super friendly, including the bar owner, Ray. He is usually present at shows and engages with fans. I love to see managers and owners excited about their business. This is always true for Ray.  Ticket prices are always very modest and because of this, I can sometimes find myself here 2-3 times per week! Even though this is a smaller venue (~300 capacity) it has two full bars. You rarely have to wait for a drink here and they have a great selection of craft beer. As I mentioned before, the sound is ALWAYS impeccable here, which makes coming back worth it every time. The acts that come into the venue range from rock to blues to bluegrass to funk to talk shows to dance tributes to cover band phenomena and even community events for the holidays. Martyrs' is a living, breathing example of one of the best music venues this city has to offer. Check it out for yourself sometime!
